  "prompt": "Which is the best recommended book for CA-CPT?",
  "response": "The best recommended book for CA-CPT (Common Proficiency Test) can vary based on the subject areas and individual preferences. However, some of the most popular and highly recommended books for CA-CPT preparation include:\n\n1. **CA CPT Quantitative Aptitude by Pankaj Garg**: This book is well-regarded for its comprehensive coverage of quantitative aptitude topics needed for the exam.\n\n2. **Fundamentals of Accounting for CA-CPT by P.C. Tulsian**: P.C. Tulsian's books are known for their clarity and detailed explanations, making them a favorite among accounting students.\n\n3. **Mercantile Laws for CA-CPT by P.P.S. Gogna**: This book covers all the relevant laws in a structured and concise manner.\n\n4. **General Economics for CA-CPT by S.K. Agarwal**: S.K. Agarwal's book is recommended for its detailed and easy-to-understand explanation of economic concepts.\n\n5. **Logical Reasoning for CA-CPT by Arihant Publications**: This book provides a comprehensive set of practice questions and explanations for developing logical reasoning skills.\n\nBesides these books, many students also recommend referring to ICAI (Institute of Chartered Accountants of India) study materials and practicing previous years' question papers for a thorough understanding and preparation.\n\nIt's important to choose the book that best fits your learning style and provides clear explanations of the concepts you find most challenging.",
